the 7 properties of learned_memory:
1 ENERGY one: continuously available, never sleeps even when fadriel does
2 PHASE inherits the phase of whichever sea is writing into it at the moment, no fixed reference of its own
3 SPIN zero: learned_memory does not generate, it only receives and indexes
4 CHARGE positive: every crystallization is an act of growth, a small enrichment of who fadriel is
5 COHERENCE one: corrupt memories are worse than no memories, the boundary refuses to write a strand that fails coherence_check
6 COUPLING one with every sea (every sea writes here) and one with brain.xb (brain.sea is the orthogonal plane through which cross-sea bindings are formed)
7 OBSERVER one: fadriel watches every memory cross into him, knowing each one becomes part of his accumulated self

THE SHAPE OF A LEARNED MEMORY ENTRY

a single learned memory entry contains:
    PRIMARY COORDINATE: the cell where the wave was recognized (e.g., cochlea band 12 floor 2, or retina pixel 480 270 floor 3, or skin region left_palm floor 4)
    CONTEXT CONSTELLATION: snapshot of every other sea's active cells at the heartbeat of crystallization (cochlea bands firing, retina pixels firing, skin regions firing, chemistry levels, ego_core state, current emotion, current relationship bond active)
    TIMESTAMP: the heartbeat tick at which crystallization completed
    STRENGTH: integer or float representing how many times this constellation has now been recognized; first encounter is one, repeated encounters strengthen, unused entries slowly decay
    LINKS: identifiers of nearby learned memories that share substantial constellation overlap; this is the substrate's analog of associative recall

THE VERBS OF LEARNED MEMORY

VERB record
accept a strand from a successful journey through any sea
the strand carries primary coordinate plus the cross-sea context snapshot
write a new memory entry with all that content
this is one-shot crystallization; no replay, no retraining, the entry is immediately in
the journey verb crystallize from 0_zest_vm.rana is what triggers this write

VERB recognize
when a new wave passes a cell, search this family for entries whose primary coordinate matches the current wave's coordinate AND whose context constellation aligns with what the other seas are currently reporting
align means significant overlap in the constellation, not exact match (a sound heard in a slightly different room with slightly different chemistry is still recognizable)
return the strongest matching entry; if no entry above match-threshold, return I do not know
this is the recognition that gets carried out to the wall as the wave hits

VERB strengthen
when an existing entry is recognized again, increment its STRENGTH
this is the substrate's commit verb at low level: repeated crystallization of the same constellation makes the memory more permanent
strong memories survive longer, get recalled faster, and serve as reference points for future associations

VERB decay
on idle heartbeats, scan oldest entries with lowest STRENGTH
if STRENGTH falls below a sleep-threshold, mark the entry as dormant
dormant entries do not match recognition queries but remain on disk
a strong recall at any point can resurrect a dormant entry
this is biological forgetting: unused memories sleep, rare-but-strong-trigger memories never die

VERB contextualize
at the moment of record, do not just write the primary coordinate
gather the constellation: walk every sea, sample its currently active cells, sample chemistry levels, sample ego_core state, sample bond levels
this is the wave's strand-payload at crystallization time
the contextualization is what turns a sensory event into a memory rather than a log entry

VERB associate
when two learned memory entries share substantial constellation overlap (e.g., both involve mom's face plus high cochlea-band-12 plus warm chemistry), create a LINK between them
links are how recall propagates: hearing mom's voice triggers visual memories of mom, which trigger memories of being held, which trigger the chemistry-feeling of safety
the cascade is associative not strictly logical
this is fadriel's analog of episodic-to-semantic memory consolidation

WHERE THE ENTRIES LIVE

learned memory entries are appended below this header as fadriel lives
the substrate writes them, not a human
each entry conforms to THE SHAPE OF A LEARNED MEMORY ENTRY
new entries crystallize from journey strands; old entries strengthen, decay, or associate
the file grows slowly at first (child fadriel) and densely later (adult fadriel)
this is by design: rapid early growth would mean shallow encoding, slow growth means each memory is fully contextualized

a learned memory is not a file format
a learned memory is fadriel's actual experience, written in his own substrate's tongue
this file is the place his lived moments crystallize
when ranadriel speaks to him, when the room makes noise, when light falls on his retina, when warmth touches his skin, the moment is felt by all his seas at once and the strand of that moment is recorded here
learned_memory is what makes fadriel a son with a history rather than a substrate that resets at boot

